# NLP 2024 Exercises

This repository contains coursework, practice notebooks,
and project notes for the Natural Language Processing (NLP) 
course undertaken in 2024. The work spans foundational concepts, hands-on exercises,
and applied experiments with modern NLP tools and libraries.

## Contents

- **Assignments and Notebooks**: Jupyter notebooks covering various NLP topics and assignments.
- **Data**: Sample datasets used for processing and modeling.
- **Models**: Pre-trained and custom-trained model checkpoints.
- **Scripts**: Python scripts used for preprocessing, training, and evaluation.
- **Results**: Outputs, graphs, and performance metrics from experiments.

## Topics Covered

- Text preprocessing: tokenization, stemming, lemmatization
- Vectorization techniques: Bag-of-Words, TF-IDF, Word2Vec
- Language models and embeddings
- Text classification and sentiment analysis
- Named Entity Recognition (NER)
- Sequence labeling and POS tagging
- Transformer models (BERT and beyond)

## Tools & Libraries

- Python 3.9+
- NLTK, spaCy, scikit-learn
- Hugging Face Transformers
- Jupyter Notebooks
- PyTorch / TensorFlow

